-- Daimler reiterates plans to grow: paper
-- 
-- Mon Dec 24, 2007 12:27am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/24/us-daimler-growth-idUSL2345177320071224

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - German carmaker Daimler ( DAIGn.DE ) aims for higher growth and to be one of the world's most profitable car manufacturers, its chief executive told workers in a letter, Frankfurter Allgemeine Sonntagszeitung reported. 

 Chief Executive Dieter Zetsche is "confident" of achieving higher growth and profitability, he said in the letter, the German weekly paper reported in the e-mailed version of an article to be published on Sunday. Zetsche has said before that he aims for all of Daimler's operations to grow in 2008 and t resume the company's share buyback program if profitability is in line with expectations. (Reporting by  Peter Dinkloh ; Editing by  Richard Hubbard )